<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8"/>
  <title> Fudge Brownies </title>
  </head>
  <body> 
    <h1> Fudge Brownies </h1>
    <p>Get ready to whip up rich, fudgy brownies with this simple recipe that’s as fun to make as it is delicious to eat! </p>
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Fudge Brownies"/>
    <h2> Ingredients </h2>
    <ul>
      <li> 1 stick of unsalted butter</li>
      <li>1 cup of granulated sugar</li>
      <li>2 large eggs</li>
      <li>1 teaspoon of vanilla extract</li>
      <li>1/3 cup of unsweetened cocoa powder</li>
      <li>1/2 cup of all-purpose flour</li>
      <li>1/4 teaspoon of salt</li>
      <li>1/4 teaspoon of baking powder</li>
      </ul>
<h2>Instructions</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease or line an 8x8-inch baking pan with parchment paper.</li>
        <li>In a medium saucepan, melt butter over low heat. Remove from heat and stir in sugar, eggs, and vanilla until smooth.</li>
        <li>Add cocoa, flour, salt, and baking powder. Stir until just combined (don’t overmix).</li>
        <li>Pour the batter into the prepared pan and spread evenly.</li>
        <li>Bake for 20–25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not wet batter).</li>
        <li>Let cool before cutting into squares.</li>
      </ol>

  </body>
